content: I cannot predict future events. however, it is possible that other countries may follow the lead of the eu and japan and prioritize free trade. this is because free trade has been proven to boost economic growth, increase access to new markets, and improve living standards for citizens. additionally, with the rise of protectionist policies in some countries, other countries may see the advantage of maintaining or promoting free trade agreements as a way to counteract that trend. however, the decision to prioritize free trade is ultimately up to each individual country and can be influenced by a variety of political, economic, and social factors.
